properties.sfomuseum:description: Flight information packet issued by Pan American World Airways, comprising:a. folder; bi-fold format with two pockets;b. timetable (NOTE: housed separately in TT38);c. luggage label envelope; white and blue;d, e. luggage labels promoting Hotel Quitandinha, Brazil (2 copies);f. luggage label promoting the International Exposition for Industry and Commerce in Quitandihnha;g. luggage identification tag for Eves travel service, Argentina; round label with name “Spitz” filled in;h. postcard with full color photographic image of Guatemalan women carrying earthen jugs;i. flyer with list of items available from the cabin crew; double-sided sheet;j. Spanish-English dictionary; multipage booklet;k. postcard with full color photographic image of Mayan pyramids of Chichen Itza, Yucatan;l, m, n. luggage labels; blue and white oval labels with airline servicemark (3 copies);o. voucher from Metropolitan Travel Service Voucher for a tour of South America, addressed to Mr. A.C. Meyer, dated February 2, 1949; stapled folder covering single-sided green sheet;p. map of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil; fold-out format;q. English-Portuguese dictionary; multipage booklet;r, s. luggage labels promoting Hotel Quitandinha, Brazil (2 copies, same as d and e).
